<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>QPR are taking a keen interest in one of non-league's hottest prospects, Sorba Thomas of Boreham Wood.</p>

<p>The 21-year-old former West Ham academy product has been earning rave reviews from league scouts with his performances on the right wing and as a wing-back.</p>

<p>QPR director of football Les Ferdinand, who himself was plucked from non-league football, has a track record of developing lower league talent and is looking to strengthen his squad amid interest from Crystal Palace and Celtic in Bright Osayi Samuel. </p>

<p>QPR are interested in one of non-league's hottest prospects, Sorba Thomas of Boreham Wood</p>

<p>The 21-year-old former West Ham academy product (right) has been earning rave reviews</p>

<p>However, QPR face competition from Charlton Athletic and Barnsley who are selling winger Jacob Brown to Stoke City.</p>

<p>The athletic Thomas started out as a striker before converting to the wing where National League Boreham have utilised his strength, pace and skill to good effect.</p>

<p>He has established himself quickly as a crowd favourite and in turn has caught the eye of league scouts keen to unearth a bargain who recognise hims as one of the brightest talents in the division.</p>

<p>Thomas has one year left on contract but amid increasing interest, Boreham are anticipating offers before the window shuts next month.</p>

<p>QPR director of football Les Ferdinand has a track record of developing lower league talent</p>
